  },
  {
    question: "Can Absorb LMS handle both employee and customer training?",
    answer: "Yes. Absorb's multi-portal architecture lets you serve different audiences — employees, customers, and partners — from one platform. Its eCommerce portal supports course sales, and Absorb Infuse embeds learning elements into external applications. If you need one platform for all audiences, Absorb is the pragmatic single-platform choice."
  },
  {
    question: "How much do Absorb LMS and Skilljar cost?",
    answer: "Absorb's median contract value is approximately $20,000/year across verified deals. Skilljar starts at approximately $30,000/year for 1,000 monthly active users on the Essential tier, with Professional tier running $52,000–$85,000/year. Neither publishes transparent pricing — both require sales conversations."
  },
  {
    question: "Which platform has better AI features?",
    answer: "Absorb LMS has more mature AI capabilities today, including Absorb Intelligence for content recommendations, Absorb Aura for AI-enabled learning, and smart administration tools. Skilljar's AI features are newer and more limited, though the Gainsight acquisition positions it for rapid AI evolution in customer education specifically."
  },
  {
    question: "Does Skilljar have a mobile app?",
